f course allowed to ask questions or voice opinions, even disagree, but this form of manipulation will not be accepted.<br>
<br>
As officers and as a guild we believe that people guildremoving or threatening to guildremove in the heat of the moment is not something that should be done lightly. We recommend that people upset over an issue give time to weigh the consequences of removing themselves from the guild before actually doing so. Turning off guildchat, going anon or just logging off and cooling down is usually the best way to get a clear perspective on a situation. We ask that anyone upset do any or all of these things and take some time before doing anything this rash.<br>
<br>
